                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/22/2004&nbsp;: 06:21:59 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> I'm a player who likes to do as much damage as possible in a short space of time. Even with FD this often got me into trouble as hard hitting mobs summoned me and thrashed me a bit until I got FD off.<br /><br />So I train Spell Casting Subtlety to rank 2 and more recently rank 3 because the description says it reduces aggro by 20% (at rank 3) on spells cast. However, it seems to me that whilst it works really well on DD spells and allows me to pretty much chain nuke, I still get huge aggro from DoTs. My suspicion is that it actually only affects DDs and doesn't make a whit of difference to DoTs which kinda sucks.<br /><br />For example I can chain nuke PoEarth mobs but if I open with FP and follow with BoT I get summoned before I can begin casting FD. Which isn't ideal when mobs are hitting as hard as they do there.<br /><br />Has anyone found the same thing with this AA or got any info on how it works?</span></font></td>
